Walt Disney Co. Chief Executive Bob Iger has scaled the mountain.
Through a series of sure-footed moves, Iger has worked tirelessly to position Disney as the world’s preeminent entertainment company.
Advertisement“This is a game changer for the industry,” Jessica Reif Ehrlich, media analyst at Bank of America’s Merrill Lynch, said in an interview.
The message was: ‘You either need to get bigger — or get out.’ ”Iger sought the Fox assets to fortify Disney against the onslaught from the north.
The Fox assets are key to Iger’s strategy of operating several streaming services, including the family oriented Disney+, which is scheduled to launch later this year.